    <text>
        <body>
            <entry xml:id="entry_art" xml:lang="os">
                <form xml:id="form_d5685e66" type="lemma"><orth>art</orth></form>
                <sense xml:id="sense_d5685e69"><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                        <q>огонь</q>
                    </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                        <q>fire</q>
                    </abv:tr></sense>
                <abv:exampleGrp xml:id="exampleGrp_d5685e79">
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d5685e81">
                        <quote>arxajy jæ artyl īw sawdæræg ūs</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>возится над огнем женщина в трауре</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>a woman in mourning over the fire</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>43</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d5685e100">
                        <quote>art banʒærstoj qædy</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>развели костер в лесу</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>they made a fire in the forest</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Munk."/><biblScope>60</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d5685e119">
                        <quote>K˳yrdalægon yn zaǧta: „æz dæ bajsærdin, fælæ dy basūʒʒynæ
                            arty“</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>Курдалагон сказал: «я закалил бы тебя, но ты сгоришь в огне»</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>Kurdalagon said: “I would temper you, but you will burn in fire”</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_ОЭ"/><biblScope>I 18</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d5685e138">
                        <quote>xūrmæ dær næ xūs kæny, artmæ dær næ</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>не сохнет ни на солнце, ни на огне</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>it dries neither in the sun nor on fire</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_ОТ"/><biblScope>32%l25%l</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d5685e157">
                        <quote>cyraǧ æmæ art nyxx˳yssyn kæn, xæʒary rūxs k˳yd næwal wa, aftæ</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>загаси лучину и огонь, чтобы в доме не было больше света</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>extinguish the splinter and fire so that there is no more light in
                                the house</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_ОЭ"/><biblScope>I 88</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d5685e177">
                        <quote>K˳ycykk artyl arxajdta, mæqījy sæddæntæ artyl ænʒærsta</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>Куцык возился с огнем, подкладывал в огонь обломки сапетки</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>Kutsyk fiddled with the fire, put the pieces of skep on the fire</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Сека"/><biblScope>75</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d5685e196" xml:lang="os-x-digor">
                        <usg><lang/></usg>
                        <quote>arti qwæcæmæ xanī kosgutæ ærcudæncæ</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>на дым костра пришли слуги хана</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>the khan's servants came to the smoke of the fire</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_MSt."/><biblScope>12%l3%l</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d5685e218" xml:lang="os-x-digor">
                        <usg><lang/></usg>
                        <quote>mæ arti wazal!</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>гибель (остывание) моего очага!</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>the death (the cooling) of my hearth!</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <note type="comment" xml:lang="ru"> (выражение ужаса, отчаяния)</note>
                        <note type="comment" xml:lang="en"> (an expression of horror,
                            despair)</note>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Iræf"/><biblScope>89</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d5685e247">
                        <quote>dæ art æmæ xsonæj zyng acæǧd</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>твоим огнивом и кремнем высеки огонь</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>strike fire from your flint with your fire steel</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_ЮОПам."/><biblScope>III
                            48</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                </abv:exampleGrp>
                <re xml:id="re_d5685e267">
                    <form xml:id="form_d5685e269" type="lemma"><orth>artag</orth></form>
                    <sense xml:id="sense_d5685e272"><sense xml:id="sense_d5685e273"><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                                <q>топливо</q>
                            </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                                <q>fuel</q>
                            </abv:tr></sense><sense xml:id="sense_d5685e282"><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                                <q>горючее</q>
                            </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                                <q>petrol</q>
                            </abv:tr></sense></sense>
                    <abv:exampleGrp xml:id="exampleGrp_d5685e292">
                        <abv:example xml:id="example_d5685e294" xml:lang="os-x-digor">
                            <usg><lang/></usg>
                            <quote>artag afojnadæbæl sæ kʼoxi ne ʽftudæj</quote>
                            <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                                <q>горючее не попадало к ним вовремя</q>
                            </abv:tr>
                            <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                                <q>fuel did not reach them on time</q>
                            </abv:tr>
                            <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_FS"/><biblScope>V
                                65</biblScope></bibl>
                        </abv:example>
                    </abv:exampleGrp>
                </re>
                <etym xml:lang="ru">Закономерная перестановка из <hi rendition="#rend_italic">*atr</hi> (ср. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_fyrt"/> ‘сын’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_7rtæ"/> ‘три’);
                    восходит к <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d5685e495" xml:id="mentioned_d5685e324" xml:lang="ira"><lang/>
                        <w>*ātar-, *aθr-</w>
                        <gloss><q>огонь</q></gloss></mentioned>; ср. <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d5685e503" xml:id="mentioned_d5685e332" xml:lang="ku"><lang/>
                        <w>ār</w></mentioned>, <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d5685e508" xml:id="mentioned_d5685e337" xml:lang="ps"><lang/>
                        <w>or</w></mentioned>, <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d5685e514" xml:id="mentioned_d5685e343" xml:lang="prc"><lang/>
                        <w>âṛ</w></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Morgenstierne._IIFL"/><biblScope>I 235</biblScope></bibl>),
                        <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d5685e523" xml:id="mentioned_d5685e352" xml:lang="yai"><lang/>
                        <w>āl</w>
                        <gloss><q>огонь</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d5685e531" xml:id="mentioned_d5685e360" xml:lang="x-rushani"><lang/>
                        <w>arθōn</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru"> (←
                            <hi rendition="#rend_italic">*aθr-dāna</hi>)</note>
                        <gloss><q>очаг</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d5685e541" xml:id="mentioned_d5685e370" xml:lang="x-rushani"><w>aθēr</w>
                        <gloss><q>зола</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d5685e547" xml:id="mentioned_d5685e376" xml:lang="x-rushani"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>пепел</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_РТ"/><biblScope>57</biblScope></bibl>), <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d5685e558" xml:id="mentioned_d5685e387" xml:lang="mnj"><lang/>
                        <w>yūṛ</w></mentioned>, <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d5685e563" xml:id="mentioned_d5685e392" xml:lang="zza"><lang/>
                        <w>adir</w></mentioned>, <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d5685e568" xml:id="mentioned_d5685e397" xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>aδar</w></mentioned>, <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d5685e573" xml:id="mentioned_d5685e402" xml:lang="pal"><lang/>
                        <w>aδur, atur</w></mentioned>, <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d5685e578" xml:id="mentioned_d5685e407" xml:lang="xco"><lang/>
                        <w>’rw</w></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Henning._Khwar."/><biblScope>13</biblScope></bibl>), <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d5685e588" xml:id="mentioned_d5685e417" xml:lang="sog"><lang/>
                        <w>*ātr-(ʼʼtr), *ārt (ʼrδ)</w></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Reichelt"/><biblScope>ZIIIV 247</biblScope></bibl>. —
                            <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Morgenstierne._IIFL"/><biblScope>II
                            273</biblScope></bibl>), <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d5685e601" xml:id="mentioned_d5685e430" xml:lang="xbc"><lang/>
                        <w>ΑΘΡΟ</w></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_JRAS"/><biblScope xml:lang="ru">1953, стр. 110</biblScope></bibl>), <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d5685e612" xml:id="mentioned_d5685e441" xml:lang="ae"><lang/>
                        <w>ātar-, āθr-</w>
                        <gloss><q>огонь</q></gloss></mentioned>. В <hi rendition="#rend_bold">скифском</hi> собственном имени
                        <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d5685e620" xml:id="mentioned_d5685e449" xml:lang="xsc"><lang/>
                        <w>ίατραγόρας</w></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Латышев"/><biblScope>II 56</biblScope></bibl>), может быть, можно видеть в
                    первой части <hi rendition="#rend_italic">*atr</hi> ‘огонь’, а во второй — <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d5685e629" xml:id="mentioned_d5685e458" xml:lang="os"><lang/>
                        <w>agur-</w>
                        <gloss><q>искать</q></gloss></mentioned>. Ср. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ærtxūron"/>, д. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ærtdor"/>.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Миллер_Вс._ОЭ"/><biblScope>II
                            49</biblScope></bibl>; <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Miller._Gr."/><biblScope>41</biblScope></bibl>. —
                            <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Hübschmann._Oss."/><biblScope>24</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>52, 158, 213</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
                <etym xml:lang="en">A regular inversion from <hi rendition="#rend_italic">*atr</hi> (cf. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_fyrt"/> ‘son’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_7rtæ"/> ‘three’);
                    traces back to <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d5685e324" xml:id="mentioned_d5685e495" xml:lang="ira"><lang/>
                        <w>*ātar-, *aθr-</w>
                        <gloss><q>fire</q></gloss></mentioned>; cf. <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d5685e332" xml:id="mentioned_d5685e503" xml:lang="ku"><lang/>
                        <w>ār</w></mentioned>, <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d5685e337" xml:id="mentioned_d5685e508" xml:lang="ps"><lang/>
                        <w>or</w></mentioned>, <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d5685e343" xml:id="mentioned_d5685e514" xml:lang="prc"><lang/>
                        <w>âṛ</w></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Morgenstierne._IIFL"/><biblScope>I 235</biblScope></bibl>),
                        <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d5685e352" xml:id="mentioned_d5685e523" xml:lang="yai"><lang/>
                        <w>āl</w>
                        <gloss><q>fire</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d5685e360" xml:id="mentioned_d5685e531" xml:lang="x-rushani"><lang/>
                        <w>arθōn</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="en"> (←
                            <hi rendition="#rend_italic">*aθr-dāna</hi>)</note>
                        <gloss><q>hearth</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d5685e370" xml:id="mentioned_d5685e541" xml:lang="x-rushani"><w>aθēr</w>
                        <gloss><q>ash</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d5685e376" xml:id="mentioned_d5685e547" xml:lang="x-rushani"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>ashes</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_РТ"/><biblScope>57</biblScope></bibl>), <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d5685e387" xml:id="mentioned_d5685e558" xml:lang="mnj"><lang/>
                        <w>yūṛ</w></mentioned>, <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d5685e392" xml:id="mentioned_d5685e563" xml:lang="zza"><lang/>
                        <w>adir</w></mentioned>, <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d5685e397" xml:id="mentioned_d5685e568" xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>aδar</w></mentioned>, <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d5685e402" xml:id="mentioned_d5685e573" xml:lang="pal"><lang/>
                        <w>aδur, atur</w></mentioned>, <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d5685e407" xml:id="mentioned_d5685e578" xml:lang="xco"><lang/>
                        <w>’rw</w></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Henning._Khwar."/><biblScope>13</biblScope></bibl>), <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d5685e417" xml:id="mentioned_d5685e588" xml:lang="sog"><lang/>
                        <w>*ātr-(ʼʼtr), *ārt (ʼrδ)</w></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Reichelt"/><biblScope>ZIIIV 247</biblScope></bibl>. —
                            <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Morgenstierne._IIFL"/><biblScope>II
                            273</biblScope></bibl>), <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d5685e430" xml:id="mentioned_d5685e601" xml:lang="xbc"><lang/>
                        <w>ΑΘΡΟ</w></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_JRAS"/><biblScope xml:lang="en">1953, p. 110</biblScope></bibl>), <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d5685e441" xml:id="mentioned_d5685e612" xml:lang="ae"><lang/>
                        <w>ātar-, āθr-</w>
                        <gloss><q>огонь</q></gloss></mentioned>. In a <hi rendition="#rend_bold">Scythian</hi> proper name
                        <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d5685e449" xml:id="mentioned_d5685e620" xml:lang="xsc"><lang/>
                        <w>ίατραγόρας</w></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Латышев"/><biblScope>II 56</biblScope></bibl>), may be <hi rendition="#rend_italic">*atr</hi> ‘fire’ in the
                    first part, and <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d5685e458" xml:id="mentioned_d5685e629" xml:lang="os"><lang/>
                        <w>agur-</w>
                        <gloss><q>look for</q></gloss></mentioned>in the second part. Cf. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ærtxūron"/>, Digor <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ærtdor"/>.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Миллер_Вс._ОЭ"/><biblScope>II 49</biblScope></bibl>;
                            <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Miller._Gr."/><biblScope>41</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Hübschmann._Oss."/><biblScope>24</biblScope></bibl>. —
                            <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>52, 158,
                            213</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
            </entry>
